.TH "lpfc_register_new_vport" 9 "lpfc_register_new_vport" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_register_new_vport \- Register a new vport with a HBA
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" lpfc_register_new_vport
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ","
.BI "struct lpfc_vport *vport "  ","
.BI "struct lpfc_nodelist *ndlp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
pointer to lpfc hba data structure.
.IP "vport" 12
pointer to a host virtual N_Port data structure.
.IP "ndlp" 12
pointer to a node-list data structure.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine registers the \fIvport\fP as a new virtual port with a HBA.
It is done through a registering vpi mailbox command.
